snippet.textDisplay:
N100 refereed to as "maintenance free respirators" has an "assigned protection factor" of 10 which means leakage of the mask can be expected even when a "fit test" has been conducted. In addition there is no protection for the eyes and even if goggles are worn they must be "chemical splash goggles otherwise like the maintenance free respirators, leakage can be expected. Garden variety goggles are practically useless.
Without proper training on how to disposed of the respirator, contamination can occur when the N100 is removed i.e. the naked hand used to remove the respirator. These were the major reason healthcare workers were infected early on with SARs in 2003, even though they were wearing maintenance free respirators. A much higher protection factor can be expected with Powered Air Purifying Respirators (PAPR) but expensive. Once PAPR's were required during the SARS epidemic, healthcare workers were no longer reporting personal contamination.

Ideally, Supplied Air Respirators (SAR) offer the highest protection since clean air is supplied and not depending on filtration.

The virus travels with the aerosolized sneeze or cough. The face shields seen worn on the news are of little protection since they do not seal around the face i.e. chemical
splash goggles.

Supplied Air Respirators, preferably full face supplied air respirators, should be the personal protection of choice. Much of what is being seen is offering a false sense of protection.

Maintenance Free Respirators offer little protection other than keeping the users hands away from the mouth and nose and offer zero protection from contamination by way of the eyes.

If the user is exposed to the coronavirus, the chances are that the outside surface of the respirator is a culture of the virus waiting for the users un-gloved hand to remove the mask.

Without proper training on how to disposed of the respirator, contamination can occur when the N100 is removed i.e. the naked hand used to remove the respirator. These were the major reason healthcare workers were infected early on with SARs in 2003, even though they were wearing maintenance free respirators. A much higher protection factor can be expected with Powered Air Purifying Respirators (PAPR) but expensive. Once PAPR's were required during the SARS epidemic, healthcare workers were no longer reporting personal contamination.

Ideally, Supplied Air Respirators (SAR) offer the highest protection since clean air is supplied and not depending on filtration.

The virus travels with the aerosolized sneeze or cough. The face shields seen worn on the news are of little protection since they do not seal around the face i.e. chemical 
splash goggles.

Supplied Air Respirators, preferably full face supplied air respirators, should be the personal protection of choice. Much of what is being seen is offering a false sense of protection.

Maintenance Free Respirators offer little protection other than keeping the users hands away from the mouth and nose and offer zero protection from contamination by way of the eyes.

If the user is exposed to the coronavirus, the chances are that the outside surface of the respirator is a culture of the virus waiting for the users un-gloved hand to remove the mask.
